VIP - 100X Crypto Signals & Analysis by Bryan x MineStack
$DIONE sell targets:

My first targets for taking profits are at $0.014 which is roughly 20X from when I first purchased. $0.014 is a $140million market cap (roughly). Currently Dione is at 38million.

After selling enough to cover my initial risk... everything above that is just free money.

My maximum sell price is $1.00 ($10billion market cap)
And in between is a whole lot of orders (there's more if i scroll up, but the screenshot only allows me to show you this many).

How I sell is this:
- at $140million market cap (which is still very cheap for DIONE), I sell just enough to return my money (that's 8% of supply for me). so out of 100% of my DIONE, I now have 92% when I sell at 0.014.

Each order afterwards I sell 25% of remaining supply so...
25% of 92% sold at 0.15 = 69% remaining supply.
25% of 69 sold at 1= 51,75% remaining supply.
25% of 51,75% 0.05= 38,8125 remaining,
etc.
Until my final 3 orders, they go 33% of remaining, 50% of remaining, 100% of remaining. (My final 3 orders are not on this screenshot. I couldn't fit them on one screen.)

If you do the math on the above example, you'll understand WHY I place my orders at intervals of 10X (roughly) each order. so 0.014, 0.15, 1.

This is because i'm selling 25% of REMAINING SUPPLY so I want big orders at each major milestone - 140million marketcap, 1.5Billion marketcap and 1billion marketcap.
After that each order afterwards gets smaller, and smaller, that's why I DON'T sell from smallest value to highest, but in groups of 10Xs.

Anyway, DIONE is up to around 0.004 today. we purchased at 0.0008 so we're up 5X so far... first profit target should be coming soon.

DISCLAIMER: Not financial advice. Buying Crypto has the risk of losing your initial capital. You are accountable for your own actions

10% BTC

"sell end of 2025" but we will be giving a more exact timing of when we exit later when it gets closer to the actual date.

VIP - 100X Crypto Signals & Analysis by Bryan x MineStack
EXIT STRATEGY:
Once you buy a coin, immediately place limit sell orders.

For example. If I buy DIONE at $0.00287...
I will place limit sell orders of:
25% sold at 0.0287 (10x)
25% sold at 0.287 (100x)
etc.

The example I gave above is ONLY an example so you understand the concept. By placing a limit sell order, you don't need to remember to sell the coin. It will automatically sell once the price hits your target.

This is very very important, otherwise you will forget to take profit and sell your coins.

I generally will sell like this.

Let's say I buy 1000 coin X:
333 I will sell at 5X buy price
222 I will sell at 50X buy price
111 I will sell at 10X buy price
The rest I will just leave it until 2025.

Because if the first 3 targets are hit, I will already bag profits. If the first 5X target is hit, My position is now zero risk.

That's the GENERAL rule but there are exceptions. For example, my first target on RIO is 10X because it's currently at just $4million market cap. it will EASILY do a 10X if not 100-1000X.

Hopefully the exit strategy makes sense. If you are confused or need clarification. ASK QUESTIONS. there's no point buying coins and forgetting to sell them. you must SELL to make a profit.

The only coins you can forget to sell are Bitcoin, DOGE and ETH. Everything else MUST be sold by the end of the cycle.

VIP - 100X Crypto Signals & Analysis by Bryan x MineStack
A member asked to clarify the sell target concept:

Example: if I Buy 1000 coin XXX at $1.

Set SELL LIMIT order:
333 at $5
222 at $50
111 at $100 etc
The rest i sell either when its clearly too expensive or at the end of 2025.

The third 111 target i will often change to suit the marketcap of the coin. Sometimes at 10x 20x etc.

And of course this is only a guide. If the coin has a very low marketcap my first target is often 10x not 5x. If the coin is like UBXS that has a marketcap of just $5million my first target is 100x

So use your head when setting targets but the important point is to set the sell limit orders IMMEDIATELY. Otherwise you will forget. Its hard to track 50-100 coins individually. And setting sell limit orders gives you a concrete plan that should never change

VIP - 100X Crypto Signals & Analysis by Bryan x MineStack
Good question from a new member.

Regarding sell limit targets for new members.

The price you buy is most likely already higher than when we bought because almost everything has gone up.

But to judge your first target, simply check the marketcap of each coin on coinmarketcap or coingecko.

There are 2 marketcaps.

Circulating marketcap (CM)

Fully diluted marketcap (FDM)

For most coins the one we want is FDM.

the exceptions are gamefi tokens, and Proof of Work tokens and a few odd exceptions where we look at the CM not the FDM.

But basically 95% of the coins on our list were purchased under 100m marketcap. So first target at or under 1bn is fine (ie. 10x first target)

More often than not its usually around 500m marketcap first target.

But you look at the marketcap now compared to 1bn marketcap. How many X‚Äôs are left?

If u bought when its at 500m marketcap. A first target of 5bn is quite high and relatively more risky. So consider a 5x first target.

Does that make sense?

VIP - 100X Crypto Signals & Analysis by Bryan x MineStack
Im happy members are asking detailed questiond about exit strategy because thats the important thing. U cash in ur profits when they become profits.

Answering this question:

No.

First sell target is only to take back initial risk. Usually a 5-10x sometimes 20x but at this stage of the cycle theres no more 20x first targets left.
Amount at 10x is 10%. Amount if its a 5x is 20%.

After first target achieved, theres no more risk even if that coin dumps to 0.

Second sell target is the maximum potential target. So if a coin has 100x potential, thats my second target. 20-25% of leftover stock at 100x

Third fourth fifth sixth targets are each at 25% of remaining stock and is spread between lowest and highest targets.

The rest at end of 2025 to capture any potential ‚Äúover exceeding expectations‚Äù

The idea is to scale out as the coin climbs. But after first target its already a risk free bet anyway

Does that make sense?

VIP - 100X Crypto Signals & Analysis by Bryan x MineStack
https://www.coindesk.com/business/2024/03/26/crypto-exchange-kucoin-violated-anti-money-laundering-laws-us-charges/amp/

KuCoin and 2 founders charged for criminal activity.

But is this the same as Binance with CZ?

I‚Äôm not sure.

We would have to see.

But we mitigate the risk of any 1 exchange going under with 2 ways
1. The coins that are on exchange because of sell limit orders stay there, but we spread our capital across several exchanges so if something goes bad on 1 exchange its not all our money gone on that 1 bad exchange

2. the coins not resting on limit sell orders get withdrawn to cold storage (ledger nano x or trezor safe 3)

By doing it this way, we make sure that at least not all our money is gone if an exchange ends up becoming a problem.

Kucoin is one of the biggest exchanges and has zero history of problems, but we will soon find out who truly controls the customer funds there over the next few days. If the 2 founders charged go to jail and turns out they control the keys to customer funds then that could be an issue.

But if they handle it professionally like CZ did with Binance then it should be fine.

Its a wait and see, and plan for the worst type game.

That being said, I personally just tested a small withdraw of NAVI which was on KuCoin, it did take 2 hours to process, but it did come through fine.
09:27
I highly recommend if you HAVE NOT withdrawn your coins that are not on resting sell limits, to withdraw them out to cold storage - MOST tokens are either BSC or ERC20 tokens meaning you can withdraw to the Binance Smart Chain (BSC) address or to the Ethereum address - but make sure you have ETH/BNB on those wallet address so you can transfer the tokens back out of your ledger/trezor.

TEST A SMALL AMOUNT FIRST - like... $10 worth. make sure you receive it in the correct wallet, AND make sure if its your first time you test sending the coin back out from the wallet back to the exchange. Make sure you understand both sides of receiving and sending, AND THEN withdraw the bigger/full amounts

If you are super confused, comment. if necessary I will record a tutorial, but there should be plenty of tutorials on YouTube
09:27
some tokens, like RIO on OKEX is on XLM - that requires technical skill to do it - i'll probably have to record a tutorial for that one
09:42
Photo
1280√ó100
Also, if you need to cancel sell limit orders (maybe because you set sell limits on 100% on your coins), I recommend creating a spreadsheet like this: Listing which orders you cancelled, the price and the quantity.

I would cancel the limit orders with the most optimistic targets (so if i bought a coin at $0.10 and set my limits at $100 and 1000 i would cancel those first).

And as the resting orders get filled when the coins go up, I would then transfer over from ledger at future date, to then reinstate the cancelled orders... if that makes sense.

Again, I understand I'm typing quite a lot of things here, so if any of this is confusing, please comment and be specific which part you are confused about so I can give you the necessary support and attention.

Also comment "understood" or similar if you understand.

I personally as a general rule of thumb set sell limits on only around 50% of my position (give or take). The rest goes in cold storage until end of 2025. That's just how i've always done it. But I understand members here do different things

VIP - 100X Crypto Signals & Analysis by Bryan x MineStack
woah woah woah GUYS!

I'll tell you what... instead of accidentally losing your crypto transferring incorrectly...

It's better to just show up to Livestream #11 which is being hosted on the MineStack YouTube Channel for Insider members on the 7th April 2024.

You can join using this link:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC4xSImWr_bod8dqkvjGyaxw/join
EDIT: Sign up as an Insider, and then the link for LS#11 is on our community posts.

The short answer is this:
1. Transferring from exchange to wallet MUST use the network native to your coin. For Bitcoin that's the Bitcoin network... for ETH that's the ERC20 network... for BNB and Binance Smart Chain tokens that's the BSC/BEP20 network...

etc.

2. TRANSFERRING from exchange to your ledger/trezor using the WRONG network will lose your money permanently.

3. That's why I said in big capital letters to test a small amount first. so that if you screw up, you only lose a small amount.

4. If it's your first time using a ledger/trezor you should also test transferring from Ledger back to exchange to make sure you understand how to transfer in both directions.

5. Only after you've confirmed to successfully withdraw/deposit in both directions... then go for the full amount.

for Indonesian members, watch this video:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cooQo1z2Hc4

And seriously... if you have a sizable portfolio. Let's say....... anything above $10K USD... just bloody join Livestream #11... Have I ever disappointed you with the knowledge I give?

In the meantime... if you are concerned with Kucoin's drama... transfer what coins you can to Binance/other exchanges in the short term just for this week as we wait for 7th April's LiveStream.

The demo will use a brand new Trezor wallet though the same steps would work on Ledger too
üëç
4
13:43
So here's an example of coins that are ERC20 tokens. On my ledger, I click on the ETH wallet, receive, the address I get given is the ERC20 network address for all coins on the Ethereum network... WHICH INCLUDES ETHEREUM.

But it also includes coins like DIONE, NAVI, ROUTE, etc.

So when I'm on the exchange and I click withdraw coin DIONE for example...

I will select the ERC20/Ethereum network, and transfer to the ETH address on Ledger.

My Ethereum wallet on ledger must have a balance of ETHEREUM on it so I can transfer the DIONE back to the exchange later on.

This strategy of using cold wallets is ONLY appropriate if you have a sizable portfolio. Because gas fees is approx $20 one way. $40 to ways. And that price could go up/down depending on how busy the network is.

I've seen $150 gas fees in the 2021 cycle peak.

So again... transferring to cold wallet is ONLY for people with sizable portfolios (say, $1000 or more worth of any 1 coin)

Can you help me calculate some basic math?

How does one start with $1000 and get to $1million?

One way is to get lucky on one coin that does 1000x‚Ä¶

Another way is to get 1 coin that does 10x to $10k, then rollover that $10k to coin #2 that also does a 10x to $100k

And then roll over that 100k to a third coin that also does a 10x to $1million.

Another way is to turn 1k into 10k from coin #1

Keep 1k in btc for safety, and rollover 9k to coin #2 that does 10x to 90k.
Keep 9k in btc then roll over 81k to coin #3 that does 10x to 810k.
And then find just 1 coin to double and put 200k there. Keep the rest in btc for safety.

Indonesian Explanation on Compounding

Part 1 was published publically, here it is:
https://youtu.be/OJ6Q3kM4DHo?si=ORqlvSJ3ku-trmIZ

Part 2 is this video attached above.
In summary: As coins climb up - for example. a coin that started at $1 with a 100x target of $100...

Once it hits $5-$10 that triggers our first take profit orders to recoup our initial risk.

That initial risk can be held as USDT (no compounding)...

Or it can be held in Bitcoin/DOGE/ETH (simple compounding).

Or it can be compounded to other alts that haven't yet done their 5-10x's.

Or a combination of the above.

Use this post as a forum for asking questions. it's important you truly understand the concepts before execution, because there is a RISK of loss if you execute incorrectly.

Happy learning.

BTC.D Chart is heading down, which is the signal for Altseason starting.

But price wise, most of our alts are still below pre-BRC levels.

I personally think there should be 1 more "shakeout" where BTC flash dips to trigger short sells at the bottom AND to force weak hands to sell before the real pump begins.

This would translate to the BTC.D chart moving up before really going down sharply.

But.

I don't make my financial decisions based on what I think will happen in days.

I make decisions based on weeks and months.

Look back at our history.

I thought a BRC would happen in January, February and March. I was wrong all 3 times. But I continued to keep buying and DCA'ing no matter what.

I thought ATH would not come until late 2024 because historically that's ALWAYS been the case.

I never sold a single coin unless it hit my profit targets...

And I kept on buying and DCA'ing.

And so my portfolio kept going up... and up... and up... because my timeframe was in months - everything I bought since October through to April is cheap compared to prices in 2025.

So regardless of what price does 1-3 weeks from now... if I were hypothetically not 100% in yet... I would DEFINITELY be 100% in by end of April, or if I wanted to stick to that 10th May deadline then sure... I could do that too.

The rest is just patience. Patience in the form of months, not days.

The future is very bright.

Happy buying.

A warning to first timers experiencing their first cycle.

MOST people lose their money not during the altseason, but right after they made easy money off of a coin that did a moonshot.

Weekly bar baru akan muncul hari ini. Jalur yang paling memungkinkan adalah sebuah ‚Äúbull trap‚Äù. Keatas dulu buat bentuk ekor keatas, drop lagi buat liquidasi/hajar long positions yang pakai leverage.

Intinya ini momen2 yang mana market makers ada goal yaitu hajar liquidation sebanyak2nya both shorts diliquidate dan longs di liquidate jg .

Logikanya simple. Kalau kamu mau trading futures pakai 1M, terus di liquidate terus2an jadi sisa hanya 50jt‚Ä¶ nah disitu exchange sudah senang. Silahkan long lagi dan kali ini the real bull run happens, karena kamu yg cuma sisa 50jt paling cm bs kembali ke 1M dengan long position, sedangkan exchange bisa pakai 950jt km beli spot cuan berlipat.

Make sense?

Off course itu ilustrasi yg di simplify biar konsepnya masuk, realitasnya ada both long dan shorts y harus di hadapin sm exchange.

But thats why i know most likely short term correctionnya belum beres. Sih exchanges belum cuan cukup banyak wkwkwk.

Best chart to see exchanges liquidating the dumb money is on the 4 hourly chart. Because the easiest people to liquidate are short term intraday traders.

One of the key reasons I always say don't trade. Be happy with 10x, 50x, 100x. It's already so much more profitable than any other asset class without the need for leverage.

But it's very easy to see where the losing traders lose their money.

The harder thing to read is when exchanges are done taking their money.

Because we don't have insider information on the exchange side, we don't know how much capital clients have left on exchanges, and how much has been liquidated.

Good morning. Here's another DCA strategy to consider (There's no right or wrong, just personal preference).

Besides having "Price" targets, have time targets.

So for example.
"If BTC price hits 55K, I'm all in 100% no DCA, just buy all in and wait for 2025."
OR
"If BTC does not hit 55k, now is 24 July 2024, I want to be all in by latest 31 August 2024, so that's 5 weeks, each week I DCA 20% regardless of price.

And so you have a plan to be all in by August 2024, but also a plan to buy with everything you have at a certain target price.

Again, this is only an IDEA for consideration, it's not me telling you to do exactly that. We did something very similar during Oct23-Apr24.

A member here has notified that he has issues with Coinex not providi g its services to (I assume) Indonesia.

I‚Äôll first give ideas for the exchange issue, then important principles around crypto storage.

Exchange side:
1. Try good quality VPN. I use Nord and Astrill both are paid. Astrill is so good it works even in China.
2. Try different internet provider and repeat step 1.
3.Ask support to withdraw out of exchange if still having issues with vpn.
4. If still issues, If big funds. Move to another country see if that works. Not an option for small funds and busy people.

Crypto storage principles:
I GENERALLY (but not always) keep half stock on exchange and half stock in private custody (hard wallet).

1. Ledger is generally more user friendly but I use both Ledger and Trezor
2.ALWAYS test first withdraw small amount from exchange to hardware wallet AND THEN send from hardware wallet to exchange to make sure you sent it right in both directions.
3. Then send the big amount
4. How you store depends on which network your coin is on. Too many for me to list. We have a Livestream recording dedicated to crypto storage so just check the recording and watch it.

Keep your private keys and secret phrases safe. I have a whole set of videos explaining how.
